<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/353</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Guatemalan Special Mission</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Toledo
                                    Herrarte</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-03"><hi rend="italic">January 3,
                                        1921</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                                your Excellency that the Government of Guatemala has been pleased to
                                bring to an end the Special Mission with which I have been
                                entrusted, for a settlement of the boundary dispute with the
                                Republic of Honduras.</p>
                            <p>In expressing to your Excellency my profound gratitude for the kind
                                and untiring attentions that your Honorable Government has deigned
                                to extend to me during my Mission, I take [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Luis Toledo
                                Herrarte</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>